   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>s<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>pāṇḍukampa</supplied>l</w><w>pārenā</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>swāryāṃ</w><w>karel<supplied>ṣināṃ</supplied></w><w><supplied>waśenyo</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a4"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>yäksātär</w><w>ñäkc<supplied>yā</supplied>ṃ</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>pä</supplied>lkoñcäs</w><w>krā<supplied>ṃ</supplied></w><w>päśśä<supplied>ṃ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>sasyuṣ</w><w>yiñc</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>ñäkciṃ</w><w>ā</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b4"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>ptā<supplied>ñkät</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... on a (<hi>pāṇḍukambala</hi>) throne ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (with) a sweet laughing (voice) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... embraces divine ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having seen outer skin, breasts ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they go (= become?) satiated ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... divine ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the Buddha ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Faint traces of black ruling.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment"><hi>(pāṇḍukampa)l pārenā</hi>: cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a187"/> b5, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a301"/> a8, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a308"/> a5, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a315"/> b4.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">: for the restoration, cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/><citedRange>104a</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment"><hi>yäksātär</hi>: the reading follows <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegetal1931"/><citedRange>459</citedRange></bibl> and <bibl><title corresp="ref:malzahn2010"/><citedRange>791</citedRange></bibl>. <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/><citedRange>185b</citedRange></bibl> rather reads <hi>ksātär</hi> 'blinds' or 'is blinded'. This is indeed an option, but no subjunctive of <hi>ksā-</hi> is attested otherwise; it is also possible that <hi>kākso</hi> was an isolated, frozen preterite participle without accompanying finite forms.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment"><hi>lkoñcäs</hi>: theoretically, options are <hi>(kä)lkoñcäs</hi>, <hi>(pä)lkoñcäs</hi>, <hi>(mä)lkoñcäs</hi>, <hi>(sä)lkoñcäs</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">: for the restoration, cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/><citedRange>171a</citedRange></bibl>.</note></p>
         </div>
